args: Make a line, people!\nAnd no cutting!
Hey, guys? I'm glad you're doing so well,\nbut could you do something about your\nline? It's blocking our stand.
We'll take care of the queue now. My\ndeepest apologies for the troub—aaah!
Heh! Thanks for the dosh, babe!
Wait, Rodrigo! Jakob!\nIf you both go after her—
Excuse me! Is my order ready yet?
Oh, my apologies! It's just about up.
(As glad as I am to be so busy...\nHow am I supposed to handle all these\npeople by myself?)
*sob* Mommy... I can't find my mommy!\nWAAAAAAAH!
A lost child... Heavens, what do I do?\nI can't just ignore her.
Hey, is my order STILL not ready?\nI've been waiting forever, y'know.
I-I'm so sorry! It should only be a little—
(This is quickly spiraling out of control!)
Sorry to keep you waiting. We managed to\nget the money back. Are you doing okay?
Jakob! Rodrigo! Sorry, but can\nyou mind the stand for me?
I need to take this little girl to the\nsecurity station.
*pant* *pant* I'm back...\nI didn't realize how far it was.
Cleo! Oh, thank goodness you're here.
We've almost sold out! We need to\nwhip up some more product, and fast!
What?! But I made so many.\nHow can we already be running out?
Never mind. I'll go prepare some more.\nYou two, keep watching the stand.
Aren't you tired, Cleo? You should\nat least stop and drink some water.
I haven't the luxury to rest.\nWe mustn't keep our customers waiting.
Hey, now. The afternoon sun is at\nits hottest right now, so you really\nshouldn't push yourself.
Really, I will be fine. I'll be back shortly.
(This should be enough.\nI need to get back quickly!)
(M-maybe I should have taken a break...\nI might be at my limit.)
You know you have a weak constitution,\nCleo. Running a restaurant would be far\ntoo strenuous for you.
N-no... That's not true.\nI'm not as weak as I once was!
I don't have time to rest...no matter how\ntired I am! The customers need me.
Yeah. Sorry for running into you, Miss.
Goodness, I should be the one apologizing.\nI wasn't watching where I was going.\nAre you hurt?
No, I'm okay. But your apples, they're...
Cleo! You're back! Whoa, what happened?\nThere's something all over your yukata.
I'm so sorry. I tripped on the way back\nto the stand, and...
All the candy apples are ruined...
What's up? Everything all right, Miss?
I know you've all been waiting so long.\nBut I've ruined this batch of apples...
It is all my fault. I... I can only offer my\nsincerest apologies!
Are you freakin' kidding me? So, what,\nwe waited for nothin'? Waste of my\ndamn time... *grumble*
Now, now. She was probably just in\na hurry to get back to her customers.
Isn't that right, Miss? No need to be too\nhard on yourself for this.
Looks like all the customers are gone now,\nCleo.
I'm so sorry. You two went out of your\nway to help me with the stand, and I just...
I let down so many people today.\nThis has been an unmitigated disaster.
There are a lot of people at festivals. Just\nmakes it that much easier for accidents\nto happen. Don't beat yourself up about it.
He's right. And we can always make more\ncandy apples.
No. I'm closing down the stand.
Those were the last apples I had. One\ncannot run a business without product.
Thank you both for helping me.
The festival is still ongoing,\nso please feel free to enjoy it.
What are you going to do?
I'll...think about it after I clean up here.
No, it is fine. It is not a difficult task.\nAnd more importantly...
I just want to be alone for a little while.\nI'm sorry.
